a integrates with social networks, websites and email to publish content across platforms from one dashboard. Its CRM integration and audience segmentation ensure that each post reaches the right viewers at the right time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Monetization & Analytics</h2>\r\n<p>While the African creator economy is booming, more than half of creators earn less than ₦6,6 000 ($62) per month and only 20.7% earn from sponsored content. Sanaa Media helps change that by offering:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Integrated advertising & sponsorships:</strong> Match creators with brands and handle campaign management, invoicing and reporting.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Subscription & micro‑payments:</strong> Enable paid newsletters, premium video channels or tipping for fans via Sanaa Finance’s digital wallet and Sanaa Cards.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Data‑driven insights:</strong> Track views, engagement and conversions across platforms to refine content strategies and demonstrate ROI to sponsors.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Integration with the Sanaa Ecosystem</h2>\r\n<p>Sanaa Media works seamlessly with the broader Sanaa platform. Creators can sell merchandise on Soko 24, offer paid experiences via Tickets by Sanaa, accept payments through Sanaa Finance and Sanaa Cards, and manage community memberships via Sanaa OS. This ecosystem empowers creators to diversify income streams and control their own digital storefront.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Get Started</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Sign up for Sanaa Media on <a href=\"https://media.sanaa.co\">media.sanaa.co</a> and connect your social accounts.</li>\r\n<li>Set up your content calendar and explore AI tools for video editing or copywriting.</li>\r\n<li>Integrate your Sanaa Finance wallet to receive payments from subscribers or sponsors.</li>\r\n<li>Publish your first multi‑platform campaign and track performance using the analytics dashboard.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>With Sanaa Media, African content creators gain the tools, distribution and monetization support they need to thrive in a fast‑growing market. Join the ecosystem and transform your passion into a sustainable business.</p>\";s:12:\"content_json\";N;s:12:\"is_rich_text\";i:0;s:14:\"featured_image\";s:50:\"blogs/O0ogsbq4yHlkvkfDpor98OMcjkFoWnZTm7WZAaAX.png\";s:9:\"author_id\";i:21;s:6:\"status\";s:9:\"published\";s:8:\"featured\";i:0;s:12:\"published_at\";N;s:12:\"reading_time\";i:3;s:5:\"image\";N;s:10:\"created_at\";s:19:\"2025-11-08 21:57:34\";s:10:\"updated_at\";s:19:\"2026-01-06 11:55:03\";s:5:\"views\";i:110;s:5:\"likes\";i:0;s:6:\"shares\";i:0;s:5:\"saves\";i:0;s:9:\"bookmarks\";i:0;s:10:\"meta_title\";s:49:\"How Sanaa Media Empowers African Content Creators\";s:16:\"meta_description\";s:130:\"Sanaa Media empowers African content creators with AI tools, multi‑channel distribution, monetization and ecosystem integration.\";s:8:\"keywords\";s:92:\"Sanaa Media, African content creators, monetization, distribution, AI tools, Sanaa ecosystem\";s:14:\"ai_suggestions\";N;s:12:\"seo_analysis\";N;s:22:\"collaboration_metadata\";N;s:14:\"version_number\";i:1;s:11:\"category_id\";i:4;}s:10:\"\0*\0changes\";a:0:{}s:8:\"\0*\0casts\";a:8:{s:12:\"published_at\";s:8:\"datetime\";s:8:\"featured\";s:7:\"boolean\";s:5:\"views\";s:7:\"integer\";s:5:\"likes\";s:7:\"integer\";s:6:\"shares\";s:7:\"integer\";s:9:\"bookmarks\";s:7:\"integer\";s:5:\"saves\";s:7:\"integer\";s:12:\"reading_time\";s:7:\"integer\";}s:17:\"\0*\0classCastCache\";a:0:{}s:21:\"\0*\0attributeCastCache\";a:0:{}s:13:\"\0*\0dateFormat\";N;s:10:\"\0*\0appends\";a:0:{}s:19:\"\0*\0dispatchesEvents\";a:0:{}s:14:\"\0*\0observables\";a:0:{}s:12:\"\0*\0relations\";a:2:{s:6:\"author\";r:93;s:8:\"category\";r:168;}s:10:\"\0*\0touches\";a:0:{}s:10:\"timestamps\";b:1;s:13:\"usesUniqueIds\";b:0;s:9:\"\0*\0hidden\";a:0:{}s:10:\"\0*\0visible\";a:0:{}s:11:\"\0*\0fillable\";a:19:{i:0;s:5:\"title\";i:1;s:4:\"slug\";i:2;s:7:\"excerpt\";i:3;s:4:\"body\";i:4;s:14:\"featured_image\";i:5;s:9:\"author_id\";i:6;s:11:\"category_id\";i:7;s:6:\"status\";i:8;s:8:\"featured\";i:9;s:12:\"published_at\";i:10;s:12:\"reading_time\";i:11;s:5:\"views\";i:12;s:5:\"likes\";i:13;s:6:\"shares\";i:14;s:9:\"bookmarks\";i:15;s:5:\"saves\";i:16;s:10:\"meta_title\";i:17;s:16:\"meta_description\";i:18;s:8:\"keywords\";}s:10:\"\0*\0guarded\";a:1:{i:0;s:1:\"*\";}}i:2;O:15:\"App\\Models\\Blog\":30:{s:13:\"\0*\0connection\";s:5:\"mysql\";s:8:\"\0*\0table\";s:5:\"blogs\";s:13:\"\0*\0primaryKey\";s:2:\"id\";s:10:\"\0*\0keyType\";s:3:\"int\";s:12:\"incrementing\";b:1;s:7:\"\0*\0with\";a:0:{}s:12:\"\0*\0withCount\";a:0:{}s:19:\"preventsLazyLoading\";b:0;s:10:\"\0*\0perPage\";i:15;s:6:\"exists\";b:1;s:18:\"wasRecentlyCreated\";b:0;s:28:\"\0*\0escapeWhenCastingToString\";b:0;s:13:\"\0*\0attributes\";a:29:{s:2:\"id\";i:17;s:5:\"title\";s:49:\"Aguma Banks Ibrahim: Building the Apple of Africa\";s:4:\"slug\";s:48:\"aguma-banks-ibrahim-building-the-apple-of-africa\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:158:\"Discover how Aguma Banks Ibrahim, founder of Sanaa Co, is crafting the Apple of Africa by merging hyperlocal marketplaces, media automation & digital finance.\";s:4:\"body\";s:3561:\"<h1>Aguma Banks Ibrahim: Building the Apple of Africa</h1>\r\n<p>Aguma Banks Ibrahim, affectionately known as Aguma Banks, is the visionary founder of Sanaa Co – the integrated tech ecosystem behind Soko 24, Sanaa Media and Sanaa Finance. His mission is simple and ambitious: to craft experiences as iconic as an Apple keynote, but tailored for Africa’s unique context .</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>From a Single Printer to a Pan-African Platform</h2>\r\n<p>Aguma’s journey began humbly with a single printer and a dream. In 2018 he launched Sanaa Media to give African brands world-class automation, software and branding solutions. Today the company boasts more than 7 years in operation, a distributed team across Africa and Europe, and over 1,300 happy clients xa. The team advises, builds and scales solutions for universities, start-ups, corporates and political campaigns, always putting authenticity and local context first.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Empowering Local Commerce with Soko 24</h2>\r\n<p>Recognising that small businesses are the backbone of Africa’s economy – they account for roughly 95% of businesses, contribute 40% of GDP and provide more than half of all employment – Aguma built <strong>Soko 24</strong>, a hyper-local marketplace. Soko 24 gives merchants digital storefronts, integrated payments, logistics and analytics, while buyers enjoy area-wise search and seamless checkout. By bringing commerce online, Aguma is helping SMEs expand their reach and compete fairly in the digital age.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Democratising Media & Marketing</h2>\r\n<p>Sanaa Media remains at the heart of Aguma’s vision. The platform provides AI-driven content creation, campaign automation and analytics, letting creators and businesses across Africa plan, produce and distribute high-quality media without prohibitive costs. With Sanaa Media, artists and enterprises can build brands that resonate locally yet meet global standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Financial Inclusion Through Sanaa Finance</h2>\r\n<p>Access to capital and modern banking services is critical for growth, yet many SMEs remain underserved. Aguma responded with <strong>Sanaa Finance</strong>: digital wallets, instant payments, savings, micro-loans and buy-now-pay-later facilities all rolled into one platform. Sanaa Finance also offers Sanaa Cards for seamless spending. Across Africa, 84.4% of banks surveyed now offer mobile banking services to SME customers and 47.7% provide digital lending – but Aguma wants to ensure that African entrepreneurs can access these tools without barriers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>An Integrated Ecosystem for Africa</h2>\r\n<p>What sets Aguma Banks Ibrahim apart is his focus on building an integrated ecosystem. Soko 24 links to Sanaa Finance for instant payouts and credit scoring; Sanaa Media connects creators with customers on Soko 24 and unlocks marketing automation; Sanaa Cloud and Tickets by Sanaa further expand the suite. Under Aguma’s stewardship, Sanaa Co is delivering Silicon-Valley-grade technology and razor-sharp branding while preserving African authenticity.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Looking Ahead</h2>\r\n<p>As Sanaa Co continues to grow, Aguma remains committed to advising first and building later. Whether you’re a small trader, a university, or a multinational hotel group, his goal is to guide you to the right mix of automation, software and finance to maximise your ROI. By championing local entrepreneurs and creatives, Aguma Banks Ibrahim is steadily building the “Apple of Africa” – a homegrown tech powerhouse that empowers the continent’s businesses and communities.</p>\";s:12:\"content_json\";N;s:12:\"is_rich_text\";i:0;s:14:\"featured_image\";s:50:\"blogs/zmlUuuuFmQaIaSTSe1OSxMc7su23RhZ4nbhU35HV.png\";s:9:\"author_id\";i:21;s:6:\"status\";s:9:\"published\";s:8:\"featured\";i:1;s:12:\"published_at\";N;s:12:\"reading_time\";i:3;s:5:\"image\";N;s:10:\"created_at\";s:19:\"2025-11-08 22:19:50\";s:10:\"updated_at\";s:19:\"2026-01-06 15:25:00\";s:5:\"views\";i:169;s:5:\"likes\";i:3;s:6:\"shares\";i:0;s:5:\"saves\";i:0;s:9:\"bookmarks\";i:0;s:10:\"meta_title\";s:49:\"Aguma Banks Ibrahim: Building the Apple of Africa\";s:16:\"meta_description\";s:155:\"Learn how Aguma Banks Ibrahim, founder of Sanaa Co, built Sanaa Media, Soko24 & Sanaa Finance to empower African businesses and create the Apple of Africa.\";s:8:\"keywords\";s:157:\"Aguma Banks Ibrahim, Sanaa Co founder, Sanaa Media, Soko 24, Sanaa Finance, Apple of Africa, African entrepreneur, digital innovation, hyperlocal marketplace\";s:14:\"ai_suggestions\";N;s:12:\"seo_analysis\";N;s:22:\"collaboration_metadata\";N;s:14:\"version_number\";i:1;s:11:\"category_id\";i:4;}s:11:\"\0*\0original\";a:29:{s:2:\"id\";i:17;s:5:\"title\";s:49:\"Aguma Banks Ibrahim: Building the Apple of Africa\";s:4:\"slug\";s:48:\"aguma-banks-ibrahim-building-the-apple-of-africa\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:158:\"Discover how Aguma Banks Ibrahim, founder of Sanaa Co, is crafting the Apple of Africa by merging hyperlocal marketplaces, media automation & digital finance.\";s:4:\"body\";s:3561:\"<h1>Aguma Banks Ibrahim: Building the Apple of Africa</h1>\r\n<p>Aguma Banks Ibrahim, affectionately known as Aguma Banks, is the visionary founder of Sanaa Co – the integrated tech ecosystem behind Soko 24, Sanaa Media and Sanaa Finance. His mission is simple and ambitious: to craft experiences as iconic as an Apple keynote, but tailored for Africa’s unique context .</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>From a Single Printer to a Pan-African Platform</h2>\r\n<p>Aguma’s journey began humbly with a single printer and a dream. In 2018 he launched Sanaa Media to give African brands world-class automation, software and branding solutions. Today the company boasts more than 7 years in operation, a distributed team across Africa and Europe, and over 1,300 happy clients xa. The team advises, builds and scales solutions for universities, start-ups, corporates and political campaigns, always putting authenticity and local context first.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Empowering Local Commerce with Soko 24</h2>\r\n<p>Recognising that small businesses are the backbone of Africa’s economy – they account for roughly 95% of businesses, contribute 40% of GDP and provide more than half of all employment – Aguma built <strong>Soko 24</strong>, a hyper-local marketplace. Soko 24 gives merchants digital storefronts, integrated payments, logistics and analytics, while buyers enjoy area-wise search and seamless checkout. By bringing commerce online, Aguma is helping SMEs expand their reach and compete fairly in the digital age.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Democratising Media & Marketing</h2>\r\n<p>Sanaa Media remains at the heart of Aguma’s vision. The platform provides AI-driven content creation, campaign automation and analytics, letting creators and businesses across Africa plan, produce and distribute high-quality media without prohibitive costs. With Sanaa Media, artists and enterprises can build brands that resonate locally yet meet global standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Financial Inclusion Through Sanaa Finance</h2>\r\n<p>Access to capital and modern banking services is critical for growth, yet many SMEs remain underserved. Aguma responded with <strong>Sanaa Finance</strong>: digital wallets, instant payments, savings, micro-loans and buy-now-pay-later facilities all rolled into one platform. Sanaa Finance also offers Sanaa Cards for seamless spending. Across Africa, 84.4% of banks surveyed now offer mobile banking services to SME customers and 47.7% provide digital lending – but Aguma wants to ensure that African entrepreneurs can access these tools without barriers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>An Integrated Ecosystem for Africa</h2>\r\n<p>What sets Aguma Banks Ibrahim apart is his focus on building an integrated ecosystem. Soko 24 links to Sanaa Finance for instant payouts and credit scoring; Sanaa Media connects creators with customers on Soko 24 and unlocks marketing automation; Sanaa Cloud and Tickets by Sanaa further expand the suite. Under Aguma’s stewardship, Sanaa Co is delivering Silicon-Valley-grade technology and razor-sharp branding while preserving African authenticity.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Looking Ahead</h2>\r\n<p>As Sanaa Co continues to grow, Aguma remains committed to advising first and building later. Whether you’re a small trader, a university, or a multinational hotel group, his goal is to guide you to the right mix of automation, software and finance to maximise your ROI. By championing local entrepreneurs and creatives, Aguma Banks Ibrahim is steadily building the “Apple of Africa” – a homegrown tech powerhouse that empowers the continent’s businesses and communities.</p>\";s:12:\"content_json\";N;s:12:\"is_rich_text\";i:0;s:14:\"featured_image\";s:50:\"blogs/zmlUuuuFmQaIaSTSe1OSxMc7su23RhZ4nbhU35HV.png\";s:9:\"author_id\";i:21;s:6:\"status\";s:9:\"published\";s:8:\"featured\";i:1;s:12:\"published_at\";N;s:12:\"reading_time\";i:3;s:5:\"image\";N;s:10:\"created_at\";s:19:\"2025-11-08 22:19:50\";s:10:\"updated_at\";s:19:\"2026-01-06 15:25:00\";s:5:\"views\";i:169;s:5:\"likes\";i:3;s:6:\"shares\";i:0;s:5:\"saves\";i:0;s:9:\"bookmarks\";i:0;s:10:\"meta_title\";s:49:\"Aguma Banks Ibrahim: Building the Apple of Africa\";s:16:\"meta_description\";s:155:\"Learn how Aguma Banks Ibrahim, founder of Sanaa Co, built Sanaa Media, Soko24 & Sanaa Finance to empower African businesses and create the Apple of Africa.\";s:8:\"keywords\";s:157:\"Aguma Banks Ibrahim, Sanaa Co founder, Sanaa Media, Soko 24, Sanaa Finance, Apple of Africa, African entrepreneur, digital innovation, hyperlocal marketplace\";s:14:\"ai_suggestions\";N;s:12:\"seo_analysis\";N;s:22:\"collaboration_metadata\";N;s:14:\"version_number\";i:1;s:11:\"category_id\";i:4;}s:10:\"\0*\0changes\";a:0:{}s:8:\"\0*\0casts\";a:8:{s:12:\"published_at\";s:8:\"datetime\";s:8:\"featured\";s:7:\"boolean\";s:5:\"views\";s:7:\"integer\";s:5:\"likes\";s:7:\"integer\";s:6:\"shares\";s:7:\"integer\";s:9:\"bookmarks\";s:7:\"integer\";s:5:\"saves\";s:7:\"integer\";s:12:\"reading_time\";s:7:\"integer\";}s:17:\"\0*\0classCastCache\";a:0:{}s:21:\"\0*\0attributeCastCache\";a:0:{}s:13:\"\0*\0dateFormat\";N;s:10:\"\0*\0appends\";a:0:{}s:19:\"\0*\0dispatchesEvents\";a:0:{}s:14:\"\0*\0observables\";a:0:{}s:12:\"\0*\0relations\";a:2:{s:6:\"author\";r:93;s:8:\"category\";r:168;}s:10:\"\0*\0touches\";a:0:{}s:10:\"timestamps\";b:1;s:13:\"usesUniqueIds\";b:0;s:9:\"\0*\0hidden\";a:0:{}s:10:\"\0*\0visible\";a:0:{}s:11:\"\0*\0fillable\";a:19:{i:0;s:5:\"title\";i:1;s:4:\"slug\";i:2;s:7:\"excerpt\";i:3;s:4:\"body\";i:4;s:14:\"featured_image\";i:5;s:9:\"author_id\";i:6;s:11:\"category_id\";i:7;s:6:\"status\";i:8;s:8:\"featured\";i:9;s:12:\"published_at\";i:10;s:12:\"reading_time\";i:11;s:5:\"views\";i:12;s:5:\"likes\";i:13;s:6:\"shares\";i:14;s:9:\"bookmarks\";i:15;s:5:\"saves\";i:16;s:10:\"meta_title\";i:17;s:16:\"meta_description\";i:18;s:8:\"keywords\";}s:10:\"\0*\0guarded\";a:1:{i:0;s:1:\"*\";}}}s:28:\"\0*\0escapeWhenCastingToString\";b:0;}',1767715165),('related_posts_20','O:39:\"Illuminate\\Database\\Eloquent\\Collection\":2:{s:8:\"\0*\0items\";a:3:{i:0;O:15:\"App\\Models\\Blog\":30:{s:13:\"\0*\0connection\";s:5:\"mysql\";s:8:\"\0*\0table\";s:5:\"blogs\";s:13:\"\0*\0primaryKey\";s:2:\"id\";s:10:\"\0*\0keyType\";s:3:\"int\";s:12:\"incrementing\";b:1;s:7:\"\0*\0with\";a:0:{}s:12:\"\0*\0withCount\";a:0:{}s:19:\"preventsLazyLoading\";b:0;s:10:\"\0*\0perPage\";i:15;s:6:\"exists\";b:1;s:18:\"wasRecentlyCreated\";b:0;s:28:\"\0*\0escapeWhenCastingToString\";b:0;s:13:\"\0*\0attributes\";a:29:{s:2:\"id\";i:18;s:5:\"title\";s:65:\"Soko24 Business – From Stock Shelf to Social Feed in One Click.\";s:4:\"slug\";s:60:\"soko24-business-from-stock-shelf-to-social-feed-in-one-click\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:133:\"Soko24 Business helps African SMEs sell, get paid, and get seen. One-click POS, hardware bundles and auto-generated social media ads.\";s:4:\"body\";s:1570:\"Soko24 Business – From Stock Shelf to Social Feed in One Click.\r\n\r\n\r\nSoko24 Business is an all-in-one commerce platform for African SMEs. We give small shops, boutiques, pharmacies and salons the tools they need to sell, get paid, and get seen – with software, hardware and financing in one place.\r\n\r\nWith Soko24 Business, a merchant doesn’t need separate systems for POS, stock, and marketing. Our POS/ERP connects directly to the Soko24 API so that every product in the shop – name, price, photo, discount – can instantly become a professional social media advert.\r\n\r\nFrom inside the Soko24 Business dashboard, the owner simply chooses a product, selects a template, and our \"mini-Canva\" generates ready-to-post creatives for WhatsApp, Instagram, Facebook and posters – automatically branded with the shop’s logo, colours, price tags and QR codes.\r\n\r\nKey benefits\r\n- Sell smarter – POS + inventory + basic ERP in one easy interface.\r\n- Market faster – auto-generate social media flyers from live product data via the Soko24 API.\r\n- Look professional – modern, clean templates that make even a small shop look like a big brand.\r\n- Grow with ease – works with Sanaa BNPL hardware bundles (tablets, printers, scanners) and can be paid monthly, annually, or one-off.\r\n- Stay connected – share promos directly to WhatsApp, print in-store posters, or sync with Soko24 marketplace.\r\n\r\n\r\nSoko24 Business turns every small business into a connected, data-driven, and market-ready brand – from the point of sale to the social timeline, in a few clicks.\";s:12:\"content_json\";N;s:12:\"is_rich_text\";i:0;s:14:\"featured_image\";s:50:\"blogs/OPA0SsKAGWbn3G4I2HxYVZTTg2BA43EmmDYQ1xHQ.jpg\";s:9:\"author_id\";i:21;s:6:\"status\";s:9:\"published\";s:8:\"featured\";i:0;s:12:\"published_at\";s:19:\"2025-11-19 22:03:00\";s:12:\"reading_time\";i:2;s:5:\"image\";N;s:10:\"created_at\";s:19:\"2025-11-19 22:01:31\";s:10:\"updated_at\";s:19:\"2026-01-05 21:24:27\";s:5:\"views\";i:215;s:5:\"likes\";i:1;s:6:\"shares\";i:0;s:5:\"saves\";i:0;s:9:\"bookmarks\";i:0;s:10:\"meta_title\";s:24:\"Soko24 Business By Sanaa\";s:16:\"meta_description\";s:133:\"Soko24 Business helps African SMEs sell, get paid, and get seen. One-click POS, hardware bundles and auto-generated social media ads.\";s:8:\"keywords\";s:66:\"Soko24 Business, POS, ERP, hardware, SMEs, Africa, marketing, BNPL\";s:14:\"ai_suggestions\";N;s:12:\"seo_analysis\";N;s:22:\"collaboration_metadata\";N;s:14:\"version_number\";i:1;s:11:\"category_id\";i:2;}s:11:\"\0*\0original\";a:29:{s:2:\"id\";i:18;s:5:\"title\";s:65:\"Soko24 Business – From Stock Shelf to Social Feed in One Click.\";s:4:\"slug\";s:60:\"soko24-business-from-stock-shelf-to-social-feed-in-one-click\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:133:\"Soko24 Business helps African SMEs sell, get paid, and get seen. One-click POS, hardware bundles and auto-generated social media ads.\";s:4:\"body\";s:1570:\"Soko24 Business – From Stock Shelf to Social Feed in One Click.\r\n\r\n\r\nSoko24 Business is an all-in-one commerce platform for African SMEs. We give small shops, boutiques, pharmacies and salons the tools they need to sell, get paid, and get seen – with software, hardware and financing in one place.\r\n\r\nWith Soko24 Business, a merchant doesn’t need separate systems for POS, stock, and marketing. Our POS/ERP connects directly to the Soko24 API so that every product in the shop – name, price, photo, discount – can instantly become a professional social media advert.\r\n\r\nFrom inside the Soko24 Business dashboard, the owner simply chooses a product, selects a template, and our \"mini-Canva\" generates ready-to-post creatives for WhatsApp, Instagram, Facebook and posters – automatically branded with the shop’s logo, colours, price tags and QR codes.\r\n\r\nKey benefits\r\n- Sell smarter – POS + inventory + basic ERP in one easy interface.\r\n- Market faster – auto-generate social media flyers from live product data via the Soko24 API.\r\n- Look professional – modern, clean templates that make even a small shop look like a big brand.\r\n- Grow with ease – works with Sanaa BNPL hardware bundles (tablets, printers, scanners) and can be paid monthly, annually, or one-off.\r\n- Stay connected – share promos directly to WhatsApp, print in-store posters, or sync with Soko24 marketplace.\r\n\r\n\r\nSoko24 Business turns every small business into a connected, data-driven, and market-ready brand – from the point of sale to the social timeline, in a few clicks.\";s:12:\"content_json\";N;s:12:\"is_rich_text\";i:0;s:14:\"featured_image\";s:50:\"blogs/OPA0SsKAGWbn3G4I2HxYVZTTg2BA43EmmDYQ1xHQ.jpg\";s:9:\"author_id\";i:21;s:6:\"status\";s:9:\"published\";s:8:\"featured\";i:0;s:12:\"published_at\";s:19:\"2025-11-19 22:03:00\";s:12:\"reading_time\";i:2;s:5:\"image\";N;s:10:\"created_at\";s:19:\"2025-11-19 22:01:31\";s:10:\"updated_at\";s:19:\"2026-01-05 21:24:27\";s:5:\"views\";i:215;s:5:\"likes\";i:1;s:6:\"shares\";i:0;s:5:\"saves\";i:0;s:9:\"bookmarks\";i:0;s:10:\